Defendant in custody.   
Count 1 - 1st degree recklessly endangering safety - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.  Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  
Count 3 - Fleeing an officer - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years, consecutive to the sentence imposed on Count 1.   Conditions of Extended Supervision and Probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
3) Pay restitution in the amount of $1,981.77 to Larry Hintz, 1308 S. 15th Street, Apt. 2, Manitowoc, WI  54220;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Write a letter of apology to the victim, Larry Hintz, the City of Manitowoc Police Department and the City of Two Rivers Police Department.
6) Pay costs of action $873.00;
7) Provide DNA sample and surcharge;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
On Count 3, six (6) month driver's license revocation.   
Defendant is entitled to 233 days sentence credit.
